        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 9:49PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 949 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 16 miles northwest of Zortman to near Hays.
Movement was northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hays and Lodge Pole.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
